Viva Question & Answer
Why did you select VAR(15)?

Answer:

The optimal lag order was determined using AIC, BIC, HQIC, and FPE criteria. AIC, HQIC, and FPE selected lag 15, while BIC selected lag 10. Since the majority of criteria favored lag 15 and the objective was forecasting accuracy, VAR(15) was selected as the final model.

Easy Real-Life Example

Imagine you are predicting tomorrow's Reliance stock price.

VAR(1) → Looks at only yesterday.
VAR(5) → Looks at the last 5 days.
VAR(15) → Looks at the last 15 days.

The lag selection criteria concluded:

"To predict tomorrow's stock price accurately, the previous 15 days contain the most useful information."

That's why your model became VAR(15). 📈


AIC, HQIC, and FPE identified Lag 15 as the optimal lag because it provided the best balance between model fit 
and forecasting performance, so VAR(15) was selected for stock price forecasting.

